  "time_ut": 1611559275,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0da9\u0dba\u0dbd\u0ddc\u0d9c\u0dca \u0da7\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc2\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dad\u0db8 \u0da0\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dbd\u0dba \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d91\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca  Activate \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Activate Dialog Television favorite channel with a miss call",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Dialog Television gives its customers the opportunity to activate their favorite channel with a missed call.",
        "For the first time in the history of Pay TV television services in Sri Lanka, Dialog Television, the leading Pay TV network in Sri Lanka, has introduced to its customers the unique facility of activating any channel or channel package of their choice from any telephone network with one missed call.",
        "Empowered customers with this new service can now activate a channel or channel package of their choice by giving one missed call to the phone number registered to their Dialog TV account.",
        "Customers can activate a desired channel by giving a missed call to 0760079XXX from a number registered with Dialog TV. When availing this service, the last 3 digits ('xxx' above) must be specified for the channel number they wish to activate and for channel numbers starting with a value less than 100, 0 must be applied at the beginning. For example, if a Dialog TV customer wants to activate the Ten Cricket (Channel No. 69) channel in his channel, he can activate the channel by giving a missed call to 0760079069 from a registered phone. The same method should be followed to activate the channel packages. The monthly fee related to the activated vans will be added to the customer's bill.",
        "In this regard, Dialog Television's Head of Business, Chirantha De Soysa commented as follows. \"We are happy to be able to introduce the latest method of easily activating a channel or a channel package of their choice to customers with one missed call. For the first time in Sri Lanka, the customer has the full freedom to decide what they want to watch and the period they want to watch, and through this, the customer also gets the experience of activating a channel more easily without any hassle.\"",
        "Customers can update their registered phone number by dialing 1777. In addition to activating the channel of your choice through the Miss Call service, you can also activate a channel of your choice by dialing 679 via SMS, using our IVR service, MyDialog App or dialog.lk. In order to activate a desired channel through the Miss Call service, the customer's Dialog Television account must be active and must have sufficient account balance."
      ],
